OL,3,CAutism and ADHD waiting lists in Wales
OL,4,C'could triple in two years'
OL,6,FThe Welsh Government has a target of
OL,7,F80% of children and young people
OL,8,Freceiving an assessment in 26 weeks,
OL,9,Ftwice as long as the 13 weeks
OL,10,Frecommended by NICE guidelines.
OL,12,FHowever, while data on waiting times
OL,13,Fis not routinely published, unlike in
OL,14,FEngland, it is thought the 80% target
OL,15,Fhas not been met Wales-wide since it
OL,16,Fwas introduced nearly a decade ago.
OL,17,FWelsh ministers have no corresponding
OL,18,Ftarget for adult assessments.
